news.title: SC refuses to relax GRAP stage IV curbs until AQI shows improvement in Delhi
news.para: Observing the Delhi-NCR faced a similar situation every year between October and December, the bench proposed to go into all aspects that cause air pollution and find a permanent solution.

news.title: Cochin development body delays repairs for Mundamveli apartments
news.para: Residents launched protests against GCDA after leakages were reported in the building months ago, but the authority is unable to carry out major repair works as the technical committee of state govt is yet to approve the repair works.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment project to use drones and LiDAR technology for digital survey
news.para: Drones and remote sensing technology Light Detection and Ranging (LiDAR) are being used to map the 620 acres densely populated Dharavi slums. This is to ensure accuracy, transparency, and efficiency in a redevelopment project of this scale and complexity.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government approves Visakhapatnam metro rail project phase I
news.para: ​​The first phase will consist of three corridors: Steel Plant Junction to Kommadi (34.40 km), Gurudwara to Old Post Office Junction (5.08 km), and Thatichetlapalem to Chinna Waltair (6.75 km).

news.title: House prices in UK rise 3.7% in November 2024: Nationwide
news.para: Prices rose by 3.7% in November compared with the same month last year, Nationwide said, significantly faster than October's 2.4% increase and the biggest jump since November 2022.

news.title: Vietnam court upholds death sentence for property tycoon in $27 billion fraud case
news.para: Property developer Truong My Lan, 68, was convicted this year of swindling money from Saigon Commercial Bank (SCB) -- which prosecutors said she controlled -- and sentenced to death for fraud totalling $27 billion.

news.title: CRDA clears sanction of funds for construction of major buildings in Amaravati
news.para: CRDA on Monday decided to call for tenders for various works worth Rs 11,467 crore including the construction of major buildings, in the capital region of Amaravati.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 76 lifts registered under new lift act
news.para: ​​ Out of these, 14 lifts were registered in GB Nagar and 7 were registered in Ghaziabad - these include 1 residential, 5 commercial and 1 industrial lift.

news.title: Kerala HC directs state government to examine violations of registry and patta conditions
news.para: The bench of Justices A K Jayasankaran Nambiar and K V Jayakumar issued the directive in response to a petition filed by P B Satheesh, director of Nerkazhcha, a Thrissur-based association.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to acquire 143 properties for 2.4-km road widening in Gunjur
news.para: According to sources, the civic body will widen the existing 30-metre road between Gunjur Lake and Vinayaka Theatre. The stretch is part of State Highway 35. The properties identified for acquisition also include 49 pieces of vacant land.

news.title: Drone survey of 550 sq km area completed in Delhi to curb encroachments
news.para: ​​The survey included the imagery of the entire Yamuna O Zone, which is spread across nearly 97 sqkm, and 66 unauthorised colonies. Officials said the agency was now in the process of carrying out a drone survey of the morphological ridge, having an area of nearly 111 sqkm.

news.title: FKCCI urges Karnataka government to roll back stamp duty hike
news.para: The govt had in Feb this year increased the stamp duty on non-registrable documents by 200-500%. According to FKCCI, real estate and small-scale industries are reeling under increased stamp duty costs.

news.title: Meghalaya survey-ready for PMAY-G expansion: Conrad K Sangma, CM
news.para: ​​This declaration follows the completion of mapping surveyors to each village, who will serve as primary contacts for conducting surveys and updating the Awaas+ 2018 list to include previously omitted deserving households and villages.

news.title: Over 88 lakh houses delivered under PMAY-U: Government
news.para: In a written reply to a question, Union Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Tokhan Sahu said that over 1.18 crore houses have been sanctioned by the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs (MoHUA) till November 18.

news.title: Over 1,000 applications received for ownership rights at PM-UDAY camps: Delhi LG
news.para: A total of 1,028 new applications were received for ownership rights and 275 applications were approved, he said, adding that 231 conveyance deeds/authorisation slips were also executed.

news.title: Smartworks receives SEBI approval for IPO
news.para: Smartworks, a flexible workspace provider, has received SEBI approval for its IPO. The company operates in 13 cities in India and has expanded to Singapore. Keppel Ltd. is a major investor in Smartworks, having invested $29 million.

news.title: Promoters, Warburg Pincus' arm sell 19.6% stake in Home First Finance for Rs 1,728 crore
news.para: As per the bulk deal data available on the exchange, Orange Clove Investments sold 94.42 shares, or 10.6 per cent stake, in Home First Finance, while True North Fund offloaded 48.09 lakh shares, amounting to a 5.4 per cent stake in the company.

news.title: Shriram Properties' CMD gets Sebi's approval for indirect acquisition
news.para: Malayappan owns 0.08% of smallcap company Shriram Properties, whose market capitalisation is at Rs 1,874 crore.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality receives Sebi's approval for Rs 2,000 crore IPO
news.para: Ventive Hospitality, a Blackstone-backed company, has received SEBI approval for a Rs 2,000 crore IPO. The company focuses on luxury hospitality, operating properties under brands like Marriott, Hilton, and Anantara. Ventive's portfolio includes 11 assets with 2,036 keys across India and the Maldives.

news.title: Shraddha Kapoor rents 3,929 sq ft apartment in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: Shraddha Kapoor has rented this apartment spread over nearly 3,929 sq ft on the third floor of a luxury residential tower for a total term of 12 months.
